HEPATITIS A, SCHOOLS - RUSSIA (TVER)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 17 Nov 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Infectious and Parasitic Diseases News, Fri 14 Nov 2003 (translated
from Russian by Nilufar Rakhmanova) [edited]
<http://www.infectology.spb.ru/index.asp>

Russia: Hepatitis A Outbreak Among Children in Tver
-------------------------------------------------
An outbreak has been observed during the past 2 weeks in Tver. Most of
those infected are school children. According to the sanitary
epidemiological surveillance service, this is a normal occurrence during
the autumn-winter season. In Vishevolozkaya school, 8 people were
identified simultaneously as infected with hepatitis A [virus]. In
Krasnoholmskaya district school, 5 cases were observed among schoolchildren
and 7 cases in Rameshkovskaya school. Anti-epidemic measures have been set
up. Vaccination was carried out on a voluntary basis. The anti-hepatitis A
vaccine is expected to [provide protection for up to 20 years].
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The recurrent nature of these outbreaks affecting school children in
Russia suggests contaminated food or water sources. Further information
would be appreciated. - Mod.CP]
